NAME
    curl - transfer data from or to a server

SYNOPSIS
    curl [options] <url>

DESCRIPTION
    Transfers data using HTTP. Supports both internal API calls (using
    session authentication) and external URLs.

    Internal paths starting with / route through the Monk API with
    the current session's authentication context.

OPTIONS
    -X <method>
            HTTP method: GET, POST, PUT, DELETE, PATCH
            Default: GET

    -H <header>
            Add HTTP header. Can be used multiple times.
            Format: "Header-Name: value"

    -d <data>
            Request body. Use @- to read from stdin.

    -o <file>
            Write response body to file instead of stdout

    -i      Include response headers in output

    -s      Silent mode (suppress errors and progress)

    -v      Verbose mode (show request details)

    -L      Follow redirects (external URLs only)

URL FORMATS
    /api/data/users
            Internal API path (uses session auth)

    https://example.com/api
            External URL

EXAMPLES
    curl /api/data/users
        List users via internal API

    curl -X POST -d '{"name":"bob"}' /api/data/users
        Create user via internal API

    curl https://api.example.com/data
        Fetch from external URL

    curl -H "Authorization: Bearer $TOKEN" https://api.example.com/me
        External request with custom header

    select id, name from users | curl -X POST https://webhook.com/import
        Pipe local data to external webhook

    curl https://external.com/data | insert /api/data/records
        Fetch external data and insert locally

    curl -o /tmp/response.json /api/data/users
        Save response to file

SEE ALSO
    select, insert, update, delete, jq
